<br>
Do you play a video game to be the voice of right and wrong? Is the purpose of EQ to give your soul more opportunities to embrace righteousness? I don't fucking think so.<br>
<br>
You play to have fun and do shit with your friends. That is more important. That's why some people don't always do the right thing for their guild. They're there for fun. It's a pretty safe bet that the other random PCs running around are using the same thing as their motivation. That's why people &quot;look up&quot; to others who have done more content and raided harder things, experiencing more &quot;fun&quot; (disclaimer: fun in EQ has become work but addicts don't keep score so whatever).<br>
<br>
Why you'd want to be the EQ player who is the nicest guy is beyond me, you didn't buy the game to be a samaritan. Following the words of God is great for real life, but fun is the god of online games. EQ just makes that somewhat distorted because you can work both with and against people, while in a 1st person shooter your goal is to get their brains on the nearest wall.<br>
<br>
